               <p>I am a constable. On the 16th or 17th of April, I found the prisoner concealed in a lost, near Tottenham court road; he had an iron bazzle (part of a fetter) on each of his legs.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was starved to death when I was there; there is never a man there but would escape from that place if he could; I would rather be hanged than be there.</p>
